1
00:00:03,630 --> 00:00:05,570
Just disappear.

2
00:00:07,810 --> 00:00:08,810
Damn it.

3
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:57,770
- That's impressive.
- Right?

4
00:00:58,740 --> 00:00:59,900
I'm actually kind of into it.

5
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,360
The car is right there.

6
00:01:02,530 --> 00:01:04,830
- Thanks.
- Yeah, get home safe.

7
00:01:33,270 --> 00:01:34,270
Seriously...

8
00:01:34,650 --> 00:01:36,010
I'm soaked to the bone.

9
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:38,930
Why is it pouring like this?

10
00:01:54,690 --> 00:01:57,990
Is this some kind of bad omen...?

11
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Episode 1)

12
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:04,770
Staring at me while I sleep again?

13
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,160
Even though my face
and hair are a total mess.

14
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:12,950
No, they're not.

15
00:03:22,780 --> 00:03:23,780
Morning.

16
00:03:25,082 --> 00:03:26,082
Fuu.

17
00:03:43,070 --> 00:03:44,070
Ah!

18
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:46,140
It was just getting to the best part...

19
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,670
What was I just dreaming about?

20
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:06,160
Crap! ...Ow!

21
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,050
Hey, Fuu! Class is about to start.

22
00:04:17,309 --> 00:04:18,658
Seriously, what are you doing?

23
00:04:18,683 --> 00:04:20,003
Looking for your underwear again?

24
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:23,229
Uh... no, I was just about to.

25
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:23,920
(Lucky Color Chart)

26
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,890
Wednesday is orange.

27
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:31,310
Hmm... lucky orange.

28
00:04:31,773 --> 00:04:34,003
Fuu, just skip the lucky color today.

29
00:04:34,370 --> 00:04:36,430
No way, I can't.

30
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:38,109
Last time I didn't follow it,

31
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:39,689
I dropped the remote on my pinky toe

32
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:40,850
and ended up with a fracture.

33
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,279
And before that, the
pencil sharpener incident...

34
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:44,030
The exam starts in twenty minutes.

35
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,630
Wait, what?

36
00:04:45,790 --> 00:04:46,790
Hey, Ren.

37
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:47,830
What do you mean, exam?

38
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:57,260
A pop quiz.

39
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,020
If you're late for no
reason, you'll fail the course.

40
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:01,970
Are you serious?

41
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:03,140
Where did you hear that?

42
00:05:03,316 --> 00:05:04,965
Attention, everyone.

43
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:06,680
Just a quick announcement.

44
00:05:07,486 --> 00:05:08,846
In twenty minutes,

45
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,140
we'll be having an exam.

46
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,320
If you have friends who aren't here yet,

47
00:05:13,370 --> 00:05:14,370
please contact them.

48
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,690
If they don't make it in time,

49
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:19,300
they won't get credit.

50
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:20,570
The professor

51
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:21,860
told me about it earlier.

52
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,620
No way... I haven't studied at all.

53
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,700
Fuu, if you're listening,
get here in twenty minutes!

54
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:28,870
This is the worst luck.

55
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:30,220
Wait, what's wrong?

56
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:32,310
(Rental Expired)
That movie I rented yesterday...

57
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:36,930
I fell asleep halfway through.

58
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:39,810
Just give it up.

59
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,480
It's more expensive than usual.

60
00:05:44,590 --> 00:05:45,990
You shouted so suddenly,

61
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,360
I missed the turn.

62
00:05:47,790 --> 00:05:48,790
That's because...

63
00:05:48,910 --> 00:05:50,530
a huge bug just flew in!

64
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:55,990
Huh?

65
00:05:56,410 --> 00:05:57,720
Wait... where's my wallet?

66
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,000
I'll use mobile pay.

67
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:04,410
Crap, my battery.

68
00:06:13,090 --> 00:06:14,090
Um...

69
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,630
Could I borrow your charger for a second?

70
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,170
Three days after the accident.

71
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:24,390
His vitals are back to
normal. Everything looks fine.

72
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,450
If everything's fine,

73
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,700
then why won't he wake up?

74
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,670
Let's just keep observing him for now.

75
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:49,740
Hey.

76
00:06:50,530 --> 00:06:52,390
It's about time you woke up.

77
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:54,630
Sara.

78
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,150
Without Fuu, I might actually starve.

79
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:34,130
Aren't you exaggerating?

80
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:36,230
You were doing just fine before you met me.

81
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:39,090
But we've already met,
so that's not an option.

82
00:07:41,470 --> 00:07:43,830
At first, you didn't even have
the courage to hold my hand.

83
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:47,700
Have you ever thought about it?

84
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:51,160
If Sara hadn't answered that day...

85
00:07:53,230 --> 00:07:54,830
we'd be in a world where we never met...

86
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:04,090
I wouldn't be able to go on.

87
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:12,950
Seriously... my luck
is at rock bottom today.

88
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:15,559
If you weren't so obsessed
with your underwear color,

89
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,980
you wouldn't have almost been late.

90
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,630
Don't you get it?

91
00:08:19,030 --> 00:08:20,846
It's because the color was
wrong that I almost missed it.

92
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:21,830
Because the color was wrong,

93
00:08:21,831 --> 00:08:23,430
my bike broke down this morning.

94
00:08:23,820 --> 00:08:25,739
A bug made the taxi fare go up,

95
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:26,780
and I lost my wallet.

96
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:30,260
Even the limited edition curry bread
I always buy was sold out.

97
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,459
And you fell asleep
during your movie, right?

98
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:34,660
Ugh, exactly.

99
00:08:36,070 --> 00:08:37,070
Oh.

100
00:08:37,730 --> 00:08:39,520
It's that movie about parallel worlds.

101
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:41,050
It sounds pretty interesting.

102
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:42,260
It is!

103
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:45,910
The hero travels through
parallel worlds to fight evil.

104
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:48,393
He stands for justice no
matter which timeline he's in.

105
00:08:50,617 --> 00:08:52,347
Though I don't know how it ends.

106
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:55,250
It's kind of like how things are now.

107
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,180
But you know,

108
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,060
isn't Fuu's luck usually way too good?

109
00:09:00,530 --> 00:09:01,829
- Huh?
- Seriously.

110
00:09:01,830 --> 00:09:03,689
That limited edition
curry bread is super rare.

111
00:09:03,690 --> 00:09:05,446
- I've never even seen it in person.
- Right?

112
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:06,710
I wish I had some of your luck.

113
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,626
I shared some with you before, didn't I?

114
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:09,770
Thanks for that, by the way.

115
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,130
- It was delicious.
- I know, right?

116
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:13,550
I had some before too, but...

117
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:15,310
All that good luck

118
00:09:15,311 --> 00:09:17,550
is only because I stick to my lucky colors.

119
00:09:20,580 --> 00:09:21,720
But today...

120
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,240
Ah!

121
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:31,150
It's not even rainy season.

122
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,100
Orange underwear.

123
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:47,090
It's your fault I'm having such a bad day.

124
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,030
I'm just kidding. I'll go
change them right away.

125
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,780
Don't worry about me, just get better soon.

126
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:03,999
As long as my guardian angel is safe,

127
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,440
that's all that matters.

128
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,710
Yes, I'm going now.

129
00:10:33,390 --> 00:10:34,390
Wait a second.

130
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:36,480
He might be trying his best too.

131
00:10:37,210 --> 00:10:39,229
Don't say that when
you don't know anything.

132
00:10:39,230 --> 00:10:41,800
Fuu, do you already have a college in mind?

133
00:11:06,580 --> 00:11:07,580
Coming.

134
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Fuu.

135
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,250
I'm so glad you're okay.

136
00:11:49,570 --> 00:11:50,570
Um...

137
00:11:53,490 --> 00:11:54,930
If you don't mind, please take this.

138
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,440
Thank you, Fuu.

139
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,250
Ah...

140
00:12:03,450 --> 00:12:05,780
I can't believe Sara knows my name.

141
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:08,500
Isn't that obvious?

142
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:10,420
No, not at all.

143
00:12:10,890 --> 00:12:13,419
It's because you've been a
big deal since high school.

144
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:15,940
You're famous at uni too, so
of course I know who you are.

145
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:21,060
But what happened to you?

146
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:23,060
Is that all?

147
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:24,780
Huh?

148
00:12:29,190 --> 00:12:30,190
To you, Fuu, am I...

149
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,800
just some senior?

150
00:12:37,810 --> 00:12:40,480
You're the cool, popular
senior everyone knows.

151
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:57,510
Hey.

152
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:01,060
Why are you crying...?

153
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:14,710
Fuu.

154
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,510
You and I are dating.

155
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,680
What did you say?

156
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:27,850
We're a couple.

157
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,930
Um...

158
00:13:33,310 --> 00:13:34,310
I'm sorry, but...

159
00:13:35,070 --> 00:13:36,870
I'm not really good at
reacting to surprises.

160
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,360
It's the truth.

161
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,320
No, no, no.

162
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:48,809
If you said we were
dating in another world,

163
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:50,570
I might actually believe you.

164
00:13:51,610 --> 00:13:53,250
No, I still can't wrap my head around it.

165
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,200
Parallel worlds.

166
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:59,289
I just watched a movie about that recently.

167
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:00,849
Well, only half of it. Of course, I
don't actually believe in that stuff.

168
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:04,940
I didn't believe it either.

169
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:13,860
But...

170
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,300
Hello?

171
00:14:37,330 --> 00:14:38,330
Ah.

172
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,800
I'm coming back now.

173
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,760
Thanks.

174
00:15:01,970 --> 00:15:02,970
Wait.

175
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:07,070
What did you mean by that?

176
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:10,090
If you don't believe me,
I don't want to scare you.

177
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:11,700
But...

178
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:14,360
Fuu, you always keep your
wallet in your back pocket.

179
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,410
If you lost it, check there.

180
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:20,260
What...?

181
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:38,670
No way...

182
00:15:40,190 --> 00:15:41,590
How did Sara know...?

183
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,440
Welcome back, Sara.

184
00:16:46,740 --> 00:16:47,940
What is even real anymore?

185
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:52,540
What should I do...?

186
00:16:56,110 --> 00:16:57,110
Fuu.

187
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,970
No, stop.

188
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,900
Don't think about it.

189
00:17:16,113 --> 00:17:17,113
Everything is fine today.

190
00:17:37,910 --> 00:17:38,910
Hey, Ren.

191
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:42,310
I don't know.

192
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,450
I haven't even asked you anything yet.

193
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,776
I'm telling you, I don't know.

194
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:45,800
Who sent it?

195
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:47,770
And why is it all of Fuu's favorite foods?

196
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,230
My favorite foods are pretty well-known.

197
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,280
Even seniors I've never
talked to know them.

198
00:18:00,010 --> 00:18:01,490
Wow, so pretty.

199
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:03,370
Maybe something good will happen.

200
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,840
Ren.

201
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:05,980
Yeah?

202
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:08,160
- Listen to me.
- Hold on, I'm taking a picture.

203
00:18:08,590 --> 00:18:09,860
- Hey, listen!
- I said hold on.

204
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,320
Hey.

205
00:18:11,940 --> 00:18:13,546
- Hey.
- Oh, you scared me. It's just Adachi.

206
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:14,610
Hey, did you guys see him?

207
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:15,740
That beautiful prince.

208
00:18:16,330 --> 00:18:17,330
What?

209
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:21,200
That elegant, model-like pose.

210
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,379
The girls keep fixing their makeup

211
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:25,300
and walking back and forth in front of him.

212
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,720
Ah.

213
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:30,950
He's coming this way.

214
00:18:30,950 --> 00:18:31,720
Hey, what are you doing?

215
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:34,050
You're the one who called him a prince.

216
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:35,849
Why are you hiding?

217
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:38,200
It's like you're the one who summoned him.

218
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,530
Hello.

219
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,970
Sara, we meet again.

220
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,940
This is the one you
couldn't get this morning.

221
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:56,730
- It's my favorite...
- I'll be going now.

222
00:19:00,070 --> 00:19:01,080
Seriously, why?

223
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:04,200
Fuu, since when are you so
close with that gorgeous senior?

224
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,069
Is he feeding you now?

225
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:07,070
No, it's not like that.

226
00:19:12,015 --> 00:19:15,185
(Sara: It'll spill,
so make sure the lid is on tight.)

227
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:16,400
He even has my contact info!?

228
00:19:16,425 --> 00:19:19,425
(Also, even if you don't know me yet,
I'm not giving up. So brace yourself.)

229
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:23,240
What were you thinking?

230
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:31,690
What?

231
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:34,150
Running out of the hospital like that.

232
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,480
Everyone was frantically looking for you.

233
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:38,120
Sorry.

234
00:19:38,210 --> 00:19:39,730
I was just worried about my boyfriend.

235
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:43,420
You've been saying that
ever since you woke up.

236
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,120
Listen to me.

237
00:19:45,186 --> 00:19:46,746
This Fuu Yotsuba you're talking about...

238
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:49,440
As far as I know,
you've never even spoken a word to him.

239
00:19:50,836 --> 00:19:52,480
But Fuu is my lover.

240
00:19:53,290 --> 00:19:54,810
We've been together since high school.

241
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,630
Please, just go back to the hospital.

242
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,690
I'm perfectly fine.

243
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:13,690
If he doesn't know me,

244
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:17,210
then I'll just win him over all over again.

245
00:20:30,610 --> 00:20:32,490
I was supposed to be lucky today...

246
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,420
Hmm...

247
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:39,330
Parallel worlds, huh?

248
00:20:40,730 --> 00:20:42,250
I never thought of it from that angle.

249
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,030
How am I supposed to believe that?

250
00:20:45,340 --> 00:20:46,460
Someone I've never even met.

251
00:20:50,610 --> 00:20:54,600
Maybe you have met,
but you just didn't notice?

252
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,300
Huh?

253
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:02,670
Thank you.

254
00:21:03,530 --> 00:21:05,830
- Thanks for coming by so often.
- Thank you, ma'am.

255
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:09,710
Ren is always dropping these little hints.

256
00:21:10,650 --> 00:21:11,650
He's such a hint-master.

257
00:21:13,870 --> 00:21:14,870
Lucky you.

258
00:21:15,370 --> 00:21:17,680
It's rare to see you two
here at the same time.

259
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:19,820
But,

260
00:21:20,230 --> 00:21:21,520
there's only one left.

261
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:23,760
I'll let him have it.

262
00:21:26,670 --> 00:21:27,670
Here.

263
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:00,360
Just like Ren said,

264
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,650
maybe I just didn't notice him...?

265
00:22:13,690 --> 00:22:14,970
Is he really...

266
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,430
my boyfriend...?

267
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:35,960
Morning, Fuu.

268
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,320
Fuu!

269
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:48,330
Fuu, wait.

270
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,560
Fuu!

271
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:55,150
Are you upset because I touched you?

272
00:22:57,540 --> 00:22:58,540
It's not that.

273
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,640
Then why did you run away?

274
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:10,760
It's because...

275
00:23:14,990 --> 00:23:15,990
you startled me.

276
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:17,790
Startled you how?

277
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:20,219
The way you said good morning.

278
00:23:20,220 --> 00:23:22,420
It sounded like you've said
it a thousand times before.

279
00:23:23,150 --> 00:23:25,000
And I've been seeing you everywhere lately.

280
00:23:25,510 --> 00:23:27,070
Even though we only met a few days ago.

281
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:30,960
I'm sorry.

282
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,320
Why are you apologizing?

283
00:23:37,690 --> 00:23:39,630
To me, our relationship is more than this.

284
00:23:41,930 --> 00:23:42,930
But

285
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:45,640
to you, Fuu...

286
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:57,670
Well...

287
00:23:57,860 --> 00:23:59,370
Can we start over?

288
00:24:03,190 --> 00:24:04,190
Huh?

289
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:07,320
I don't want to scare you,

290
00:24:08,060 --> 00:24:09,650
or make you feel uncomfortable.

291
00:24:12,330 --> 00:24:13,330
But...

292
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:15,610
I can't just let this go.

293
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:20,140
It's okay if you don't believe me yet.

294
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:22,780
For now,

295
00:24:23,430 --> 00:24:25,160
I'll just be that popular senior to you.

296
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,040
In exchange,

297
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,270
can I ask you for one thing?

298
00:24:37,150 --> 00:24:38,150
One thing...?

299
00:24:54,190 --> 00:24:55,190
Let me court you.

300
00:24:57,300 --> 00:25:04,450
Please let me pursue you,
to make you my boyfriend,

301
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:47,350
Fuu, are you okay?

302
00:26:47,910 --> 00:26:48,910
Huh?

303
00:26:49,110 --> 00:26:50,110
Fuu?

304
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:53,360
I'll go get the doctor. Just wait here.

305
00:26:55,980 --> 00:26:56,980
It's Fuu.

306
00:26:58,420 --> 00:26:59,790
My lover...

307
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:01,950
Fuu Yotsuba.

308
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:06,810
Get some rest for now.

309
00:27:59,990 --> 00:28:05,310
